<p>i'm developing android app using "pjsip" library, i made it to integrate it inside my app and tested and made calls ,i want to create something like dialing bar when the call is in the background , where i can click it and show the call screen for example. this is one of the function i used.</p>  <pre><code>public void acceptCall(View view) {         incomingCall = true;         CallOpParam prm = new CallOpParam();         prm.setStatusCode(pjsip_status_code.PJSIP_SC_OK);         try {             currentCall.answer(prm);         } catch (Exception e) {             System.out.println(e);         }         alphaAnimation = new AlphaAnimation(1.0f, 0.3f);         alphaAnimation.setFillAfter(true);         answer.startAnimation(alphaAnimation);      } </code></pre>